As per [manage().window().maximize() method not maximize a correct window](https://bugs.chromium.org/p/chromedriver/issues/detail?id=596) using `driver.manage().window().maximize();` to maximize the `Chrome Browser` is not the optimum way. Instead use **ChromeOptions** to maximize the _Chrome Browser_ as follows:

	ChromeOptions options = new ChromeOptions();
	options.addArguments(&quot;start-maximized&quot;);
	WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver(options);

To open _Chrome Browser_ in `kiosk` mode you can also use:

    ChromeOptions options = new ChromeOptions();
    options.addArguments(&quot;--kiosk&quot;);
    return new ChromeDriver(options); 

   

As an alternative you can also use the argument **`window-size`** as follows:

	ChromeOptions options = new ChromeOptions();
	options.addArguments(&quot;window-size=1400,600&quot;);
	WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver(options);

    driver.manage().window().maximize(); 

**Replace to** 

    driver.manage().window().fullscreen(); 

And it&#39;s working

